+
+## Fix-3 changelog
+
+Addresses codex BLOCK verdict at
+`dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-2-review-20260527T135041Z.md`
+(one high, one medium, one low — all localized to D4 internal
+consistency and one stale D8 citation).
+
+- **Fix 3.1 (verdict finding 1, high).** D4's "unknown kind =
+  error" rule no longer relies on the unsupported `ELSE NULL` +
+  vec0 NOT NULL combination. The migration SQL now prefixes the
+  staged-copy with a real fail-fast preflight: a
+  `_vec0_migration_assertion(check_passes INTEGER NOT NULL
+  CHECK(check_passes = 1))` sentinel table whose INSERT computes
+  `CASE WHEN EXISTS(... kind NOT IN locked-vocab ...) THEN 0
+  ELSE 1 END`. An unknown kind drives `check_passes = 0`, the
+  CHECK constraint fires `SQLITE_CONSTRAINT` at INSERT time, and
+  `apply_one`'s ROLLBACK undoes the whole step (sentinel table
+  included). The CHECK primitive is vanilla SQLite (cited:
+  https://www.sqlite.org/lang_createtable.html#check_constraints);
+  no extension, no trigger required. Multi-statement viability
+  re-verified empirically against `apply_one` at
+  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:273-288`, which
+  calls `conn.execute_batch(migration.sql)` (line 276) — batch
+  semantics, so the preflight can be a prefix statement in the
+  same SQL string. The repopulating CASE keeps `ELSE 'article'`
+  (defence-in-depth past the assertion; justified inline in D4).
+- **Fix 3.2 (verdict finding 2, medium).** D4 no longer claims
+  a Rust-rendered `<now>` literal or any migration-build-time
+  timestamp construction. The `created_at` column is filled by
+  `strftime('%s','now')` evaluated at INSERT time inside the
+  migration SQL. The uniform-timestamp guarantee is per INSERT
+  statement: SQLite's date/time functions return the same value
+  across all rows in a single statement when no varying
+  arguments are passed (cited:
+  https://www.sqlite.org/lang_datefunc.html). The stale
+  `open_with_migrations` (`lib.rs:1119`) anchor is removed from
+  D4 — no Rust path is involved in the timestamp.
+- **Fix 3.3 (verdict finding 3, low).** D8's stale `INSERT INTO
+  vector_default_v2 ... SELECT v.rowid` proof point (left over
+  from the pre-fix-2 sibling-table draft) is replaced with the
+  staged-copy proof: rowid is the explicit JOIN key in the
+  staging INSERT (`SELECT v.rowid, ... FROM vector_default v
+  JOIN _fathomdb_vector_rows r ON r.rowid = v.rowid`), and the
+  recreated `vector_default` receives the same staged rowid in
